The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, August 31, 2004 				 Indiabulls to float asset management firm 
 A STAFF REPORTER				 	 Indiabulls president Rajiv Rattan addressing a conference in Calcutta on Monday. SBI Caps senior VP Ram Nehariya was also present. Picture by Kishor Roy Chowdhury																								Calcutta, Aug. 30: Indiabulls Financial Services plans to set up an asset management company within the next couple of years. 																								It is part of our plan to offer a diversified range of products and services to capture a greater share of an investors wallet, said Rajiv Rattan, president and chief financial officer of Indiabulls Financial Services. He was speaking at the launch of the companys initial public offering in the city.																								At present, the company has a presence in equity, debt, derivatives and commodity brokerage, depository services and distribution of insurance, mutual funds and initial public offerings. 																								Indiabulls also plans to venture into various retail financial services segments such as housing finance, consumer goods lending, non-bank deposits and insurance services. The company hopes to grow in these markets through existing companies or by promoting new subsidiaries or investing in joint venture partnerships.																								We are ideally placed as loan originator since we have a strong sales and marketing team and an extremely successful revenue generation and client acquisition model, said Gagan Banga, director of Indiabulls Financial Services. The company has already made a foray into personal loans and plans to venture into the other existing segments.																								The company is looking at acquisitions within the country and is conducting internal reviews of various target firms. 
